From James Wang Subject Re Calling all Mac gurus In article qvs t q f usenet INS CWRU Edu Charles P Cox, Jr writes Question for those familiar with Quadra VRAM I put K VRAM SIMMs in my Quadra in the slots closest to the RAM SIMM slots and I got no results whatsoever I have been told that the built in video should support at least bit and maybe bit color on a Macintosh Color Display However, the Monitors control panel still lists bit colors as the highest possible the Q will only do bit or bit color if you want the higher color depth, it's MB's of VRAM altogether for a monitor up to for a monitor, you can get bit max hope this answers your questions James Wang